<item>
            <title>[OAK-2394] Clarify handling of hidden items in ImmutableTree</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2394</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2391&quot; title=&quot;Provide API to create Tree from NodeBuilder&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2391&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2391&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it occurred to me that &lt;tt&gt;ImmutableTree&lt;/tt&gt; seem to &lt;b&gt;do not&lt;/b&gt; hide &apos;hidden&apos; nodes (&lt;tt&gt;:foobar&lt;/tt&gt;) but &lt;b&gt;does&lt;/b&gt; hide &apos;hidden&apos; properties.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=anchela&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;anchela&quot;&gt;anchela&lt;/a&gt;, could you have a look and clarify?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12767080">OAK-2394</key>
            <summary>Clarify handling of hidden items in ImmutableTree</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="angela">Angela Schreiber</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="mduerig">Michael D&#252;rig</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Tue, 13 Jan 2015 09:47:15 +0000</created>
                <updated>Fri, 23 Jan 2015 12:11:59 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Thu, 15 Jan 2015 12:48:37 +0000</resolved>
                                                    <fixVersion>1.1.5</fixVersion>
                                    <component>core</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14274994" author="anchela" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2015 09:53:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes... that&apos;s a bug; that should in any case be consistent. if i remember correctly we had that broken in the AbstractTree as well and only fixed it later on... obviously we forgot to adjust the ImmutableTree. the question is what is the expected behavior... if we claim that it&apos;s just a tree-decorator around the NodeState, we probably don&apos;t want to hide the hidden items.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14276905" author="anchela" created="Wed, 14 Jan 2015 13:33:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;initial patch that doesn&apos;t doesn&apos;t apply special logic for hidden items thus making ImmutableTree just a simple tree-wrapper around whatever the underlaying &lt;tt&gt;NodeState&lt;/tt&gt; exposes. i am pretty convinced that filtering out hidden items would have negative consequences with the various validators/editors that are making use of it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note, that this means that almost all methods of &lt;tt&gt;AbstractTree&lt;/tt&gt; need to be overridden. maybe we should consider changing the abstract tree such that it may or may not filter out the hidden items. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mduerig&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mduerig&quot;&gt;mduerig&lt;/a&gt;, what do you think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14277136" author="mduerig" created="Wed, 14 Jan 2015 16:12:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1651718&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1651718&lt;/a&gt; I added &lt;tt&gt;AbstractTree#isHidden&lt;/tt&gt; to determine for an item whether is hidden. This should help in &lt;tt&gt;ImmutableTree&lt;/tt&gt; for not having to override all methods. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14277153" author="anchela" created="Wed, 14 Jan 2015 16:21:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cool, that simplifies things a lot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14278640" author="anchela" created="Thu, 15 Jan 2015 12:48:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;revision 1652081&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14289162" author="edivad" created="Fri, 23 Jan 2015 12:11:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 1.1.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
